write provider.tf, main.tf, outbput.tf, variable.tf & terraform.tfstate files and other required tf files
# in terraform create -provider.tf
provider "aws"{
    region = "us-east-1"
}

# create main.tf for EC2 & S3 bucket
resource "aws_instance" "Practical"{
    ami = "ami-0360c520857e3138f"
    instance_type = "t2.micro"
    tags = {
      Name = "Practise"
      env = "dev"
    }
}
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "my_bucket" {
  bucket = "my-unique-practise-bucket" 
  tags = {
    Name        = "MyTerraformS3"
    Environment = "Dev"
  }
}


# run the below commands one after another used Hashicorp Language - HCL

1. terraform init -
The terraform init cmd initializes a working directory containing configuration
files and installs plugins for required provider.

2. terraform validate -
The terraform validate cmd validates the configuration files in a directory.

3. terraform plan -
The terraform plan cmd creates an execution plan, which lets you preview the changes.
In case an error encounter for provider unidentified, then follow step A.

A. aws configure
enter the access key and secrete key to login to aws console via CLI and then run terraform plan again

4. Terraform apply -
The terraform apply cmd executes the actions proposed in a terraform plan to create,
update, or destroy infrastructure.

-auto-approve -> Skips the interactive approval of plan before applying

5. Terraform destroy -
The terraform destroy cmd terminates resources managed by your terraform project.


Terraform.lock.hcl -

This is auto generated by Terraform, This file contains a record of exact version of providers and 
modules used in your Terraform Configuration.


Terraform provider -
Terraform uses provider to interface between terraform engine and the supported cloud platform.


State file - tfstate file and improtant file
The terraform state file by default, is named as terraform.tfstate and is held in the same directory where terraform is run.  
It is created after running terraform apply. The actual content of this file is a JSON formatted mapping of the resources that is defined in the configuration. 
in case the tfstate file is corrupted or deleted, then terraform will forget that with same configuration earlier it was run and 
it will run again when terraform plan is executed

terraform.tfstate.backup is taken in S3 bucket and only limited employees have access to it.
